    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 20 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The force on a charge travelling in a magnetic field is maximum when charge is",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "moving parallel to the field",
        "moving perpendicular",
        "moving at 60° to the field",
        "moving 45° to the field"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "moving perpendicular"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>The magnetic force on a moving charge is given by:</p> \\[ F = qvB\\sinθ \\] <p>Where θ is the angle between velocity (v) and magnetic field (B). The force is maximum when sinθ = 1 (θ = 90°), meaning the charge moves <b>perpendicular</b> to the field.</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electromagnetism",
      "Magnetic Force",
      "Charged Particle Motion",
      "Lorentz Force"
    ]
  },
