    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 55 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A proton moves with a velocity of \\( V = (2\\mathbf{i} - 4\\mathbf{j} + \\mathbf{k}) \\, \\text{m/s} \\) in a region with a magnetic field of \\( B = 2.0 \\, \\text{T} \\). What is the magnitude of the magnetic force this charge experiences?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "\\( 2.34 \\times 10^{-18} \\, \\text{N} \\)",
        "\\( 5.25 \\times 10^{-18} \\, \\text{N} \\)",
        "\\( 4.0 \\times 10^{-18} \\, \\text{N} \\)",
        "\\( 0.5 \\times 10^{-15} \\, \\text{N} \\)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\( 1.28 \\times 10^{-18} \\, \\text{N} \\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "The magnetic force is given by \\( \\mathbf{F} = q \\mathbf{v} \\times \\mathbf{B} \\). For a proton \\( q = +e = 1.6 \\times 10^{-19} \\, \\text{C} \\). The cross product magnitude is \\( |\\mathbf{v} \\times \\mathbf{B}| = |(2\\mathbf{i} - 4\\mathbf{j} + \\mathbf{k}) \\times (2\\mathbf{k})| = |(-8\\mathbf{i} - 4\\mathbf{j})| = \\sqrt{(-8)^2 + (-4)^2} = \\sqrt{80} \\, \\text{m/s} \\cdot \\text{T} \\). Thus, \\( F = (1.6 \\times 10^{-19}) \\cdot \\sqrt{80} \\cdot 2 \\approx 1.28 \\times 10^{-18} \\, \\text{N} \\). (Note: Correct answer not listed; closest is option (a)."
    },
