  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 58 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "For moving charges, they experience a magnetic force in a magnetic field.",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "\\( F_B = q \\cdot v \\cdot B \\)",
        "\\( F_B = q v B \\)",
        "\\( F_B = q \\mathbf{v} \\times \\mathbf{B} \\)",
        "\\( F_B = q v (B) \\)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\( F_B = q \\mathbf{v} \\times \\mathbf{B} \\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "The magnetic force on a moving charge is given by the cross product \\( \\mathbf{F}_B = q (\\mathbf{v} \\times \\mathbf{B}) \\), where \\( \\times \\) denotes the vector cross product. This ensures the force is perpendicular to both velocity and field."
    },
    "topic": [
