  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 59 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Alpha particles are accelerated from rest through a potential difference of 1.0kV. They then enter a magnetic field \\( B = 0.20 \\, \\text{T} \\) perpendicular to their direction of motion. Calculate the radius of their path. (\\( M_a = 6.68 \\times 10^{-27} \\, \\text{kg}, q = +2e \\))",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "0.064m",
        "0.016m",
        "0.030m",
        "0.032m"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "0.032m"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "1. **Energy from potential difference**: \\( K = q \\Delta V = (2e)(1000 \\, \\text{V}) = 3.2 \\times 10^{-16} \\, \\text{J} \\).  \n2. **Velocity**: \\( v = \\sqrt{\\frac{2K}{M_a}} = \\sqrt{\\frac{6.4 \\times 10^{-16}}{6.68 \\times 10^{-27}}} \\approx 3.1 \\times 10^5 \\, \\text{m/s} \\).  \n3. **Path radius**: \\( r = \\frac{M_a v}{qB} = \\frac{(6.68 \\times 10^{-27})(3.1 \\times 10^5)}{(3.2 \\times 10^{-19})(0.20)} \\approx 0.032 \\, \\text{m} \\)."
    },
    "topic": [
